  <bioghist id="aspace_63a220f7e9af8d8f1a9fb44fb2857ae6">
    <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
<p>Isidore Wisotsky (1895-1970) was born circa 1895 and immigrated from Latvia to the U.S. with his family when he was fourteen. He worked in the garment industry, became an anarchist, was involved with the Industrial Workers of the World, and became a friend of Norman Thomas.</p>  </bioghist>
  <acqinfo id="aspace_28c45a2137e59b42b1608e2ee2105da1">
    <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
<p>Donated by Abraham Wisotsky, brother of Isadore Wisotsky, 1977. The accession number associated with this gift is 1997.068.</p>  </acqinfo>
